‚Ä¶

5\. A taxidermied bear, its muzzle missing. Mechanical parts protrude from the
hole. If it could sing, it would.

6\. A void, absent of form or light.

7\. A flawless reflective pane of glass. A mirror.

8\. A wild dog. Its eyes are large, spinning spirals of incandescent sparks.
It hunts.

Inside a glass display: An exceptionally heavy scepter, laden with excessive
ornamentation. Grasping the handle is troublesome and getting it through
doorways is inconvenient.

5\. A taxidermied bear, its muzzle missing. Mechanical parts protrude from the
hole. If it could sing, it would.

6\. A void, absent of form or light.

7\. A flawless reflective pane of glass. A mirror.

8\. A wild dog. Its eyes are large, spinning spirals of incandescent sparks.
It hunts.

Inside a glass display: An exceptionally heavy scepter, laden with excessive
ornamentation. Grasping the handle is troublesome and getting it through
doorways is inconvenient.

‚Ä¶

5\. A taxidermied bear, its muzzle missing. Mechanical parts protrude from the
hole. If it could sing, it would.

6\. A void, absent of form or light.

7\. A flawless reflective pane of glass. A mirror.

8\. A wild dog. Its eyes are large, spinning spirals of incandescent sparks.
It hunts.

Inside a glass display: An exceptionally heavy scepter, laden with excessive
ornamentation. Grasping the handle is troublesome and getting it through
doorways is inconvenient.

the former residence of Harlem icon Langston Hughes.

Its current owner wants to open the historic home to the public but without
any outside control.
